Here's a comprehensive Rust TCP server using Tokio with connection pooling and graceful shutdown:

## Cargo.toml
```toml
[package]
name = "tcp-server"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[dependencies]
tokio = { version = "1.0", features = ["full"] }
anyhow = "1.0"
tracing = "0.1"
tracing-subscriber = "0.3"
dashmap = "5.0"
arc-swap = "1.0"
futures = "0.3"
```

## Main Server Implementation

